##Can Wuhan Virus Get Red Xiwei Patent License? According to the patent examiners

Weixin Guokr42

Functional introductions, science and technology, are the language we speak to the world.

Gilead's antiviral drug, Remdesivir, has cured the first confirmed case of COVID-19 pneumonia in the US, according to a paper published online Jan. 31 in the The New England Journal of Medicine. At this critical moment, the good news has aroused the great concern of the general public, especially the medical workers.

And on Feb. 4, another piece of news about the drug caused a stir: the Wuhan Institute of Virology, under the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said on its website that it was based on research into drug screening at the COVID-19, cOVID-19 filed a patent for Radzivir 2019 on Jan. 21.

Screenshot of the announcement | Chinese Academy of Sciences

Is Wuhan Virus Research Institute qualified to apply for this patent? What are the prospects for them getting a mandate? What would be the impact if authorization were obtained? The shell invited a patent examiner to give her opinion.

There are two broad types of patents that can be applied for

An invention involving a drug can be patented in a variety of ways depending on the progress of its research and the need for extended protection. This is known as a "patent layout" . The patentability of drugs can be divided into two categories: product claim and method claim.

The product claim relates primarily to the right of the compound itself, such as the product claim for Ridgisivir relates to the related general formula, isomer, crystal, salt, or pharmaceutical composition of the following compound.

The structural form of Ridgeway | Meodipt Public domain

Method claims include pharmaceutical use of the compound or its preparation method, etc. . In particular, the method claims include the preparation process, pharmaceutical use, and the disease treatment method using the active compound.

Different types of patent protection granted,
The level of protection is different

Generally speaking, the protection of product category claims is stronger than method claims.

Simply put, the use, promise to sell, sell, or import of a compound for any purpose is subject to the permission of the patentee once the compound is licensed.

In general, applications for pharmaceutical uses are submitted later than applications for compounds. Thus, if, during the duration of the patent protection for a compound, the other patentee is only authorized for the pharmaceutical use of the compound, even if the latter wishes to exercise the right to that pharmaceutical use, it shall also obtain the license of the patent holder for the compound.

In turn, of course, a patent holder who holds a patent on a compound would also need to obtain a license from the patent holder who holds a patent on that pharmaceutical use in order to enforce the right to that pharmaceutical use.

Therefore, in the patent layout, the application of pharmaceutical use category is generally as a defensive patent, after the compound category patent application, mainly for extending the patent protection period.

Wuhan Virus Institute of Information also mentioned that its patent application will be through the PCT access to major countries in the world. The PCT, or patent cooperation treaty, is an international cooperation treaty designed to simplify procedures and extend lead times in multinational applications. Divided into the international stage and the national stage, the international stage is mainly to address the issue of admissibility, publication, retrieval and preliminary review; the applicant may decide whether to enter the national stage and which countries to enter specifically on the basis of the preliminary review opinion, whether or not a patent is granted in a particular country is still subject to local regulation.

The status quo of patent protection of Ridgeway

Ridgway is a antiviral drug developed by Gilead. It has completed phase III clinical trials of the Zaire ebolavirus virus and is in clinical trials for coronaviruses.

Gilead has so far requested protection in the form of a product and a treatment. Among them, application for general compounds (CN104262345B, authorization day 2017.6.23) and application for specific compounds (CN103052631B, authorization day 2015.11.25) have been authorized in China (the authorization request also includes the use of general compounds to prepare anti-HCV polymerase and to treat viral agents such as yellow fever virus and paramyxovirus) . Other types of applications do not enter China or do not go through the substantive review process.

Patent licensing for specific compounds in China | license notice CN104262345B

It is clear that Ridgeville is protected by at least the above-mentioned patents in the form of general formulas, specific compounds, pharmaceutical compositions, and pharmaceutical uses for the treatment of paramyxoviruses, among others.

Redesivir was not "snatched up" by Wuhan Virus

Any entity or individual may file an application for a patent with the patent office for a product, method or technical proposal for an improvement thereof. The Patent Office shall, after a preliminary examination and a substantive examination, make a decision on the authorization or rejection of a patent application.

Therefore, even if Gilead has already filed multiple patents for Readwriteweb, any entity or individual still has the right to file a patent application for readwriteweb on any relevant subject matter, there is nothing wrong with being legitimate for the purpose of encouraging invention and for the purpose of public health.

It may have applied for a patent for the use of COVID-192019, according to a statement posted on the website of the Wuhan Institute of Virology, Chinese Academy of Sciences. Thus, in terms of the type of application, the subject of a "new indication" in a method application, the application for a product class related to a protected compound is for a different type, which is a common type of application for a known compound, provides protection against new indications of known compounds. And radzivir specific compound category application has been authorized in China, in this sense, Radzivir is not by Wuhan Virus "rush injection. ".

Can Wuhan Virus Obtain Authorization?

Whether a patent for pharmaceutical use of a specific compound meets the licensing conditions is mainly judged by the novelty and creativity of the existing technology.

Simply put, there are several possible scenarios:

(1) the existing technology directly reveals that the specific compound can treat the disease when the new pharmaceutical application is not novel and can not be authorized.

(2) the available technology discloses the mechanism by which a specific compound can be used to treat a certain type of disease. Where a new application for pharmaceutical use can be expected to be of the same mechanism, or where there is no evidence that the new application for pharmaceutical use does not apply to such mechanism as has been disclosed, it is generally conceivable that the disease can be treated with the compound, applications for new pharmaceutical uses are not creative and can not be authorized.

(3) the prior art does not disclose the therapeutic mechanism of the compound, nor does it disclose that the compound can treat the disease. It is generally accepted that the technical staff in the field can not obtain sufficient technical inspiration and that the creativity of applications for new pharmaceutical uses may be recognized.

Types of protection for the pharmaceutical use of Ridgeway, original researcher Gilead has applied for patents for Radzivir to treat paramyxovirus infections (such as human respiratory syncytial virus and Parainfluenza) , flavivirus infections (such as dengue and yellow fever, especially Hepatitis C) , sand virus infections, coronavirus infections (such as SARS, Mers) , and filovirus infections. The patents, published before the Wuhan Virus'alleged filing date (January 21) , constitute an existing technique for determining whether the Wuhan virus'application for a new indication can be authorized.

The paper, first mentioned in the article, COVID-19, published online in Nejm on January 31st, is not part of the existing technology that the Wuhan virus applied for after the application date for its new indication, it doesn't matter if it's authorized or not.

On January 31st Nejm published an online paper showing that the antiviral drug, Remdesivir, developed by Gilead, had cured America's first confirmed case of COVID-19 pneumonia | Reuters

So the Wuhan Virus Institute of New Indications, whether it has the novelty and creativity?

Of the four Genera of coronaviruses, SARS-CoV, MERS-CoV and the Covid-192019-ncov, which is currently raging in China, belong to the genus, but "2019-nCoV" was officially named by the World Health Organization on January 12,2020, COVID-19, therefore, based on the existing technology mentioned above, it can be concluded that the 2019-nCoV COVID-19 patent is novel.

Creative judgments are less clear cut.

In judging the inventiveness of the patent for this use, it is necessary to consider the 2019-nCoV virus types and the paramyxoviruses, flaviviruses, sand viruses, filamentous viruses already disclosed in the prior art, in particular, SARS and Mers are also coronaviruses, the similarity of virus types, the consistency of treatment mechanism, the outstanding treatment activity, the selective difference of virus, the side effect and dose difference of treating different virus and so on.

An application for a patent shall mainly include a statement of claim, a specification and drawings attached thereto, wherein the specification shall include such items as the technical field, background technology, contents of the invention, description of the drawings and specific methods of implementation. Therefore, how much information is disclosed about the difference of virus and the effect of treatment in the new indication application of Wuhan Virus Institute is crucial to judge whether it can be authorized or not.

If the activity data in the specification indicate that Radicivir is relatively more active or selective for the 2019-nCoV, or that it acts on a different basis from the known SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV, wuhan Virus Institute of New Indications are expected to apply for authorization. On the other hand, it would be difficult to obtain authorization without evidence of the above-mentioned facts or any other unforeseen effects based on existing technology.

Due to the fact that the application for new indications of Wuhan Virus Institute has just been submitted, it is still at the preliminary examination stage and has not yet been made public, and the information disclosed in the specification is not yet known, so it is difficult to make an accurate judgment on the patent trend at present.

What would happen if we were authorized to do this

Currently, Ridgway's core patents are still held by the original Research Gilead Company, the patent period is still very long. Although China's patent law stipulates that "the Patent Administration Department under the State Council may grant a compulsory license for the implementation of a patent for invention in the event of a state of emergency or exceptional circumstances, or for the purpose of public interest" , but there is no precedent for compulsory licensing. Therefore, if Wuhan Virus Institute of New Indications can be authorized, the current epidemic of Red Xiwei access to medication has a positive role.

If the subject of the Wuhan Virus Application is the specific 2019-nCoV pharmaceutical use for the current outbreak, then once authorized, the possibility of cross-licensing with Gilead, in which each side grants the other access to its own patents, trademarks or know-how, gives it a say in the use of the drug.
